# Collaboration Persona
## Group goals:
  Continuously improve artifacts and process
## Group work style:
1. Program manager communicates group’s plan and status regularly with six scrum teams across three time zones
2. Developers work with engineer manager to discuss technical needs or blockers
3. Executives conducted 1-on-1 with managers to understand status, needs, blockers for teams
4. Scrum masters work with developers to understand their status, sprint plan, remove the blocks
## Collaboration needs:
1. Maintain awareness of group goals, blockers, and status across time zones and scrum teams.
2. Obtain teams’ overview to evaluate current process, practices, and artifacts
